The <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Jordanian</ENAMEX> Minister of Energy and Mineral Wealth , <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Khaled Al Shraideh</ENAMEX> , said at <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT">the Eighth Arab Conference on the Use of Atomic Energy for Peaceful Purposes</ENAMEX> , which was opened here <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">today , Sunday</ENAMEX> , that the uses of atomic energy have contibuted to all areas of life and have positively affected economic and social growth in different countries of the world , whether in combating serious diseases , improving the quality of industrial and agricultural production , producing electricity , or desalinating water .
He added that the peaceful use of atomic energy in the <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Arab</ENAMEX> world was still limited , and nonexistant in electric power production and water desalination to provide drinking water , which calls us to organized action , in order to benefit from energy to provide an important source of electricity and to provide clean water for drinking and agriculture .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Al Shraideh</ENAMEX> said that the decision to establish <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the Nuclear Energy Organization</ENAMEX> came in order to develop these uses , and to work on providing the requirements for general safety , radiation protection , and nuclear security , environmental protection and human health , and to work on building the infrastructure , and directing efforts to serve the national economy in the field of peaceful uses of atomic energy .
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Al Shraideh</ENAMEX> asked the conference participants to exert more effort to implement applied scientific research directed at finding cures and treatments for serious diseases , solving extremely difficult agricultural and industrial problems , and producing electrical energy .
For his part , the General Manager of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the Arab Organization for Atomic Energy</ENAMEX> , Dr. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mahmoud Nasr Al Deen</ENAMEX> , said that <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Arab</ENAMEX> countries have signed all international agreements aimed at preventing the spread of nuclear weapons , and that their nuclear facilities are subject to regulatory controls by <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG">the International Atomic Energy Agency</ENAMEX> .
